The @sadhev Aloe Vera & Saffron Gel is an elegantly elevated formulation. It is easily the BEST I have come across! 
⠀
It soothes and hydrates the skin wonderfully and since it’s enriched with brightening agents like Kumkumadi Tailam and Saffron; it caters to blemishes and skin tone as well. 

Crowned with saffron strands and its melded counterparts; makes this formulation a LOT more hydrating than a standalone aloe vera gel.
⠀
Best when paired with the Sadhev Rose Water which is delightfully refreshing!
⠀
Sadhev thoughtfully & ethically source ingredients from their own farm, Sadhevana, to provide each patron with the finest quality -  Which, I can 100% vouch for!

#SkincareWithSadhev

⠀
The hero ingredients of this line are anti-ageing superhero’s Ginger and Ginseng.
⠀
•The Lotus Herbals YouthRx Youth Activating Serum + Creme contains highest concentration of the revolutionary Gineplex Youth Compound.
⠀
Its lightweight formula sinks into the skin effortlessly. It is said to amp up the production collagen with consistent use to render bouncier skin in return.
⠀
•The Lotus Herbals YouthRX Anti-Ageing Nourishing Night Cream is enriched with the Gineplex Youth Compound derived from potent natural ingredients that are clinically proven to accelerate the process of lifting and forming skin.
⠀
It has a comforting and buttery texture that hydrates the skin adequately while leaving one with a notably dewy finish that’s hard not to love! 💖

IKKAI Pearl Matte Gloss is an illuminating and multifunctional strobe moisturizer. ✨🍓 @ikkai.beauty 
⠀
Use it as a primer, to moisturize your skin or on the high points of your face to add some luminosity. I’ve even mixed it in with BB cream and its worked beautifully.
⠀
The formulation is enriched with skin loving vitamins and soothing green tea. It hydrates the skin well, blends seamlessly and leaves a generous dewy glow on the skin, as if from within.
⠀
I also enjoy the tube packaging with a pump dispenser as well. This ensures that there isn’t any product wastage and one has better control over how much product seeps out.
⠀
If you’re looking for a moisturizer that amps up the glow on your skin while moisturising well, but does so at a moderate price? This one definitely serves as a great option!
⠀
Best suited for those with pink-bluish hues / cool undertones.
⠀
Those with yellow or golden hues / warm undertones on the other hand can avail the Ikkai Gold Matte Gloss which is the brands other variant.
⠀
Neutral undertoned skin people (like me) can use either. 🤍
⠀
MRP. 675 but currently on a 20% discount on the brands website and can be bought at Rs. 540.
⠀
✨Additionally; #TheIkkaiWay contest is something I’d like to make a small mention about.
⠀
The brand is giving patrons a chance to win AirPods and other exciting prizes from their range.
⠀
To enter, one can make any fun / creative skincare video using the Ikkai product of their choice, tagging the brand, using the campaign hashtag and then standing a chance to win. :)

Head on to the brand page to look into a few additional requirements.

Hello spruced up juicy lips! ft. @faebeautyofficial GLAWS GLOSS! 👄✨🍑
⠀
Bold over by the alluring packaging and innovative structure of these glosses. The clickable rollerball pen is definitely unconventional and I’m here for it!
⠀
The mechanism is such; that one needs to shake the product vigorously and then click away, maybe with an interval or two between presses?
⠀
Once I see enough product ooze out on the rollerball head is when I know it’ll make for an even distribution on my lips.  I add a little pressure and then glide the product across.
⠀
Glaws is enriched with Passion Fruit Oil and Vitamin E, is high shine and buildable. They can also be used on the cheekbones and eyelids - something that I’m yet to experiment with!
⠀
•Becoming:
⠀
Think, a bronzey cinnamon brown with hints of glittery orange. The shade is quite flattering to different Indian skin tones.
⠀
•Transforming:
⠀
Think, a transparent formula meets icy holographic specs. In my opinion, this one makes for a great topper on your favourite lipsticks!
⠀
•Emerging:
⠀
Think, bubblegum pink with specs of matching glitter. An angelic and ethereal shade that probably is my favourite from the three.
⠀
Glaws has been well priced at Rs. 499. Considering all factors that have gone into creating this line, I think that’s nice.
⠀
Like fairy dust, these glosses 
remind me of all things otherworldly and magical. Would you agree? 🧚🦄

Which GLAWS was your favourite? Let me know in the comments 🤍

#GLOWTOBER ✨ comes with exciting @pixibeauty offers on @mynykaa till the end of this month! Products are linked in my profile bio! 🥰

#PR 

 •Pixi Glow Tonic:

A gentle toner with 5% glycolic acid that deeply cleanses and gently exfoliates the skin while getting rid of impurities bedded in the pores.

Infused herein are Aloe Vera to soothe and hydrate + ginseng to protect the skin.

It is said to be safe to use daily, either in the AM or PM routine. However; if you do have sensitive skin, a couple of times a week should work best.

•Pixi Rose Glow Mist

In such a short time, this rose tinted beaut has made it to my top 3 favourite mists! 

Ingredients include 7 types of flower oils, essential fatty acids and antioxidants.

Now when I tell you this hydrates, it truly packs in that punch of moisture.

Alongside, this bi-phase mist also adds an ever so notable natural and youthful glow. 

•Pixi Glow Tonic Serum:

A glycolic Acid serum that gentlly exfoliates the skin. 

While the concentration of the same has not been disclosed, it seems to me, that it is above 5%. 

In saying that, I’d (humbly) suggest using this once or twice a week in the place of the glycolic toner but not together. 

A dollop is all you require as it is a powerful formula created so as to help one achieve a balanced and radiant complexion. 

Further, soothing hydration is provided through Aloe Extract whereas Ginseng protects the skin.

With consistent use, it is said to soften the skin and improve its texture.

•Pixi On The Glow

I absolutely adore the invention of moisture sticks! But the On The Glow moisture stick by Pixi surely takes the cake.

Why? It can be used on the hair, lips and body too; not just your face folks!  It is so sleek and ultra travel friendly. I am obsessed!

The formulation contains a unique blend of gentle acids and vitamins, including vitamin D2, one that plays a key role in protecting our skin against damage.

Pop this stick it in and out of your bag and treat your skin to bursts of moisture when required without a mess & pronto!
——— ——— ——— ———✨
Each of the above formulations are suitable for all skin types.

latestPosts.caption:
My pre-frontal cortex said NO 🙅‍♀️👇🏻
‌
•DIY skincare for cell turnover —
 lab > eyeballed oranges & lemons.
‌
Only clinically formulated actives are pH-balanced, stabilised, and tested in a manner that actually and safely reach the layers where skin renewal happens.
‌
•Law of Attraction without the work —
Setting our intentions without movement is just well wishing.
‌
•Poreless, textureless skin
..not real life. Please don’t fall for unrealistic beauty standards. Embrace your real.
‌
•Romanticising the bare minimum —
Basic human decency should be a given. Let’s not hand out gold stars for the basic
‌
•Skincare alone will fix it —
No serum outdoes mental, physical and nutritional imbalances.
‌
• “Sunscreen blocks vitamin D” or “sunscreen causes cancer” —
‌
Pseudoscience. Misinformation. Fear-mongering, dressed up as wellness.
‌
•Book smart = evolved —
‌
IQ without EQ is like activating only one side of the brain. Emotional development and self awareness is hella sexy! 😉

SAVE ✅ Banoffee Iced Latte & Caramel Recipe👇🏻
‌
Blend 1 ripe banana (the riper, the better) with 1 tsp caramel.
‌
In another bowl, mix 2 heaped spoons of instant coffee with hot water + sweetener (optional).
‌
Froth up a mix of milk of your choice and a bit of fresh cream— eyeball carefully but don’t overdo it or it’ll mute the flavour.
‌
Assemble with ice —
I went banana blend → milk froth → coffee shot. And of course a caramel drizzle (I wouldn’t say optional for that! 😋)
‌
I kept the banana mixture at the base so as to get little bites in every sip.
‌
Feel free to make this your own. Romanticize your coffee!
‌
•Quick Caramel (lasts 20–25 days):
1 cup sugar + ¼ cup water → heat without stirring till golden.

Add 3 tbsp cold butter, stir.
Turn off heat, add ½ cup fresh cream + pinch of salt + vanilla (optional)
